<datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
<subfield code="a">A new film called Sizzle: A global warming comedy could make a real difference in the fight against global warming.  In the film, actor and director Randy Olson takes on the character of a pompous scientist trying to make a straight documentary about global warming, which is quickly revealed to be a quixotic pursuit in an industry that cares more about celebrity hosts than about science.  The serious point underlying the comedy is that climate scientists need to adopt a more relaxed approach if they want to motivate the public to take the warnings more seriously.</subfield>
</datafield>
